 [ <a href="/weapons/individual/bone_bladed_claymore.shtml?ID=801&page=1"> 1 </a> ] [ <a href="/weapons/individual/bone_bladed_claymore.shtml?ID=801&page=2"> 2 </a> ] [ <a href="/weapons/individual/bone_bladed_claymore.shtml?ID=801&page=3"> 3 </a> ]</center>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Alarik Zekaiden</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-09 00:22:40</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I like this weapon because of it's solid damage/speed ratio, and it is easy to get earlier on (comparatively speaking), but that agility hit sure is nasty.  You end up having to get around 200pp worth of compensation jewelery and items to make up for it, or ignore it, and have a hard time running away from the average monster because you are slowed.  Good weapon, but a bad side-effect.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Deano</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-11 20:09:06</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Get a couple of +2 AGI earrings and you half that awful AGI hit of this weapon. Deals about 28HP of damage upto level 20 but by then you'll be looking for a Blackened Iron Bastard Sword. Overall worth the 100pp or so you'll pay for it and will serve you well through your teen levels.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Happy with my BBC</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-13 10:17:54</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This weapon rocks for a Dark Elf SK.  The speed/damage ratio is the best you're going to get through level 20.  That pesky AGI hit is easy to sqaush, just pick up a Gold Carnelian Wed. Ring (+5AGI) for about 25PP and an Onyx Earring (+2AGI) for 5PP and you're down to only -1AGI for a measly 30PP, what a deal!  :)  I actually have AGI stuff that gives me +12 total so I'm ahead of the game, best part is when I run from zone to zone I unequip it and the speed burst from +12AGI is like a SOW!  Woo-hoo! :)<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Spektor of Vallon Zek</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-20 13:34:27</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I just got my new BBC at level l5, and i must say at first i wasnt impressed, but after slashing constantly for 28-30 pts of dmg, and gettin critical hits from 50-96!!! i think its a great sword.  The AGI hit is realy harsh, but i pumped alot into my AGI specs anyway, and alot of my armor is able to give me AGI boosts.  Anyways, all in all with Double attack and a BBC i have found myself to be unstopable!  I even took out a Aviak Guard at leve l5!!! and was hunting cyclopses with my friends yesterday.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Eldarkon Andellmere</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-22 10:34:52</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Hmm, I bought my BBC from a gnome who was looking for some quick cash for 25plat and a tentacle whip, and I  must say that<BR>
it was more than worth it, though the AGI hit is kinda nasty(though I, like most warriors, spent my jewlry spots on str boosts).</font></td></tr></table>
